      "content": "The Powerhouse Design System is a collection of reusable front-end components based on GraphQL scalars. It provides:\n\n- Consistent UI components across Powerhouse applications\n- Automatic inclusion as a dependency in new projects\n- Customization via CSS variables\n- Custom scalar types tailored for the web3 ecosystem\n\nBuilt-in GraphQL scalars: `String`, `Int`, `Float`, `Boolean`, `ID`\nPowerhouse custom scalars: `OID` (Object ID), `Currency`, `DateTime`, and other web3-specific types\n\nThese scalars are more than just type definitions - they are linked to reusable front-end components from the `@powerhousedao/document-engineering` package. When you use a custom scalar in your schema, corresponding UI components are available for rendering and editing that data type.",
